{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I don't know what the hell I'm doing here."},{"time":3000,"text":"I was born in a Scots Presbyterian ghetto in Canada,"},{"time":6000,"text":"and dropped out of high school. I don't own a cell phone,"},{"time":10000,"text":"and I paint on paper using gouache, which hasn't changed in 600 years."},{"time":16000,"text":"But about three years ago I had an art show in New York,"},{"time":21000,"text":"and I titled it \"Serious Nonsense.\""},{"time":24000,"text":"So I think I'm actually the first one here -- I lead."},{"time":28000,"text":"I called it \"Serious Nonsense\" because on the serious side,"},{"time":31000,"text":"I use a technique of painstaking realism of editorial illustration"},{"time":37000,"text":"from when I was a kid. I copied it and I never unlearned it --"},{"time":40000,"text":"it's the only style I know. And it's very kind of staid and formal."},{"time":45000,"text":"And meanwhile, I use nonsense, as you can see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"This is a Scottish castle where people are playing golf indoors,"},{"time":53000,"text":"and the trick was to bang the golf ball off of suits of armor --"},{"time":57000,"text":"which you can't see there."},{"time":58000,"text":"This was one of a series called \"Zany Afternoons,\" which became a book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"This is a home-built rocket-propelled car. That's a 1953 Henry J --"},{"time":66000,"text":"I'm a bug for authenticity -- in a quiet neighborhood in Toledo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"This is my submission for the L.A. Museum of Film."},{"time":75000,"text":"You can probably tell Frank Gehry and I come from the same town."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78000,"text":"My work is so personal and so strange"},{"time":82000,"text":"that I have to invent my own lexicon for it."},{"time":84000,"text":"And I work a lot in what I call \"retrofuturism,\""},{"time":88000,"text":"which is looking back to see how yesterday viewed tomorrow."},{"time":92000,"text":"And they're always wrong, always hilariously, optimistically wrong."},{"time":97000,"text":"And the peak time for that was the 30s,"},{"time":100000,"text":"because the Depression was so dismal"},{"time":102000,"text":"that anything to get away from the present into the future ..."},{"time":105000,"text":"and technology was going to carry us along."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"This is Popular Workbench. Popular science magazines in those days --"},{"time":111000,"text":"I had a huge collection of them from the '30s --"},{"time":113000,"text":"all they are is just poor people being asked to make sunglasses"},{"time":117000,"text":"out of wire coat hangers and everything improvised"},{"time":120000,"text":"and dreaming about these wonderful giant radio robots"},{"time":123000,"text":"playing ice hockey at 300 miles an hour --"},{"time":125000,"text":"it's all going to happen, it's all going to be wonderful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"Automotive retrofuturism is one of my specialties."},{"time":132000,"text":"I was both an automobile illustrator and an advertising automobile copywriter,"},{"time":137000,"text":"so I have a lot of revenge to take on the subject."},{"time":142000,"text":"Detroit has always been halfway into the future -- the advertising half."},{"time":145000,"text":"This is the '58 Bulgemobile: so new, they make tomorrow look like yesterday."},{"time":150000,"text":"This is a chain gang of guys admiring the car."},{"time":154000,"text":"That's from a whole catalog -- it's 18 pages or so --"},{"time":156000,"text":"ran back in the days of the Lampoon, where I cut my teeth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"Techno-archaeology is digging back and finding past miracles that never happened --"},{"time":168000,"text":"for good reason, usually."},{"time":170000,"text":"The zeppelin -- this was from a brochure about the zeppelin"},{"time":174000,"text":"based, obviously, on the Hindenburg."},{"time":176000,"text":"But the zeppelin was the biggest thing that ever moved made by man."},{"time":181000,"text":"And it carried 56 people at the speed of a Buick at an altitude you could hear dogs bark,"},{"time":187000,"text":"and it cost twice as much as a first-class cabin on the Normandie to fly it."},{"time":191000,"text":"So the Hindenburg wasn't, you know, it was inevitable it was going to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"This is auto-gyro jousting in Malibu in the 30s."},{"time":200000,"text":"The auto-gyro couldn't wait for the invention of the helicopter,"},{"time":204000,"text":"but it should have -- it wasn't a big success."},{"time":206000,"text":"It's the only Spanish innovation, technologically, of the 20th century, by the way."},{"time":211000,"text":"You needed to know that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"The flying car which never got off the ground -- it was a post-war dream."},{"time":217000,"text":"My old man used to tell me we were going to get a flying car."},{"time":220000,"text":"This is pitched into the future from 1946,"},{"time":222000,"text":"looking at the day all American families have them."},{"time":225000,"text":"\"There's Moscow, Shirley. Hope they speak Esperanto!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":230000,"text":"Faux-nostalgia, which I'm sort of -- not, say, famous for, but I work an awful lot in it."},{"time":235000,"text":"It's the achingly sentimental yearning for times that never happened."},{"time":240000,"text":"Somebody once said that nostalgia is the one utterly most useless human emotion --"},{"time":247000,"text":"so I think that’s a case for serious play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"This is emblematic of it -- this is wing dining,"},{"time":254000,"text":"recalling those balmy summer days somewhere over France in the 20s,"},{"time":259000,"text":"dining on the wing of a plane. You can't see it very well here,"},{"time":262000,"text":"but that's Hemingway reading some pages from his new novel"},{"time":265000,"text":"to Fitzgerald and Ford Madox Ford until the slipstream blows him away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"This is tank polo in the South Hamptons."},{"time":276000,"text":"The brainless rich are more fun to make fun of than anybody. I do a lot of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"And authenticity is a major part of my serious nonsense."},{"time":287000,"text":"I think it adds a huge amount."},{"time":289000,"text":"Those, for example, are Mark IV British tanks from 1916."},{"time":293000,"text":"They had two machine guns and a cannon,"},{"time":295000,"text":"and they had 90 horsepower Ricardo engines."},{"time":298000,"text":"They went five miles an hour and inside it was 105 degrees in the pitch dark."},{"time":303000,"text":"And they had a canary hung inside the thing"},{"time":306000,"text":"to make sure the Germans weren't going to use gas."},{"time":310000,"text":"Happy little story, isn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"This is Motor Ritz Towers in Manhattan in the 30s,"},{"time":314000,"text":"where you drove up to your front door, if you had the guts."},{"time":318000,"text":"Anybody who was anybody had an apartment there."},{"time":322000,"text":"I managed to stick in both the zeppelin and an ocean liner out of sheer enthusiasm."},{"time":325000,"text":"And I love cigars -- there's a cigar billboard down there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"And faux-nostalgia works even in serious subjects like war."},{"time":333000,"text":"This is those wonderful days of the Battle of Britain in 1940,"},{"time":337000,"text":"when a Messerschmitt ME109 bursts into the House of Commons"},{"time":340000,"text":"and buzzes around, just to piss off Churchill, who's down there somewhere."},{"time":345000,"text":"It's a fond memory of times past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"Hyperbolic overkill is a way of taking exaggeration to the absolute ultimate limit,"},{"time":355000,"text":"just for the fun of it. This was a piece I did -- a brochure again --"},{"time":361000,"text":"\"RMS Tyrannic: The Biggest Thing in All the World.\""},{"time":364000,"text":"The copy, which you can't see because it goes on and on for several pages,"},{"time":368000,"text":"says that steerage passengers can't get their to bunks before the voyage is over,"},{"time":375000,"text":"and it's so safe it carries no insurance."},{"time":378000,"text":"It's obviously modeled on the Titanic."},{"time":381000,"text":"But it's not a cri de coeur about man's hubris in the face of the elements."},{"time":385000,"text":"It's just a sick, silly joke."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"Shamelessly cheap is something, I think -- this will wake you up."},{"time":391000,"text":"It has no meaning, just -- Desoto discovers the Mississippi,"},{"time":395000,"text":"and it's a Desoto discovering the Mississippi."},{"time":399000,"text":"I did that as a quick back page -- I had like four hours to do a back page"},{"time":405000,"text":"for an issue of the Lampoon, and I did that,"},{"time":407000,"text":"and I thought, \"Well, I'm ashamed. I hope nobody knows it.\""},{"time":409000,"text":"People wrote in for reprints of that thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"Urban absurdism -- that's what the New Yorker really calls for."},{"time":417000,"text":"I try to make life in New York look even weirder than it is with those covers."},{"time":422000,"text":"I've done about 40 of them, and I'd say 30 of them are based on that concept."},{"time":427000,"text":"I was driving down 7th Avenue one night at 3 a.m.,"},{"time":430000,"text":"and this steam pouring out of the street, and I thought, \"What causes that?\" And that --"},{"time":438000,"text":"who’s to say?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"The Temple of Dendur at the Metropolitan in New York -- it's a very somber place."},{"time":445000,"text":"I thought I could jazz it up a bit, have a little fun with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447000,"text":"This is a very un-PC cover. Not in New York."},{"time":453000,"text":"I couldn't resist, and I got a nasty email from some environmental group saying,"},{"time":458000,"text":"\"This is too serious and solemn to make fun of. You should be ashamed,"},{"time":462000,"text":"please apologize on our website.\""},{"time":464000,"text":"Haven't got around to it yet but -- I may."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"This is the word side of my brain."},{"time":473000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":474000,"text":"I love the word \"Eurotrash.\""},{"time":476000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":481000,"text":"That's all the Eurotrash coming through JFK customs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"This was the New York bike messenger meeting the Tour de France."},{"time":491000,"text":"If you live in New York, you know how the bike messengers move."},{"time":494000,"text":"Except that he's carrying a tube for blueprints and stuff -- they all do --"},{"time":498000,"text":"and a lot of people thought that meant it was a terrorist"},{"time":501000,"text":"about to shoot rockets at the Tour de France --"},{"time":503000,"text":"sign of our times, I guess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"This is the only fashion cover I've ever done."},{"time":508000,"text":"It's the little old lady that lives in a shoe, and then this thing --"},{"time":511000,"text":"the title of that was, \"There Goes the Neighborhood.\""},{"time":514000,"text":"I don't know a hell of a lot about fashion --"},{"time":518000,"text":"I was told to do what they call a Mary Jane,"},{"time":520000,"text":"and then I got into this terrible fight between the art director and the editor saying:"},{"time":525000,"text":"\"Put a strap on it\" -- \"No, don't put a strap on it\" -- \"Put a strap on it -- \"Don't put a strap on it\" --"},{"time":529000,"text":"because it obscures the logo and looks terrible and it's bad and --"},{"time":532000,"text":"I finally chickened out and did it for the sake of the authenticity of the shoe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536000,"text":"This is a tiny joke -- E-ZR pass. One letter makes an idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546000,"text":"This is a big joke."},{"time":550000,"text":"This is the audition for \"King Kong.\""},{"time":553000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":559000,"text":"People always ask me, where do you get your ideas, how do your ideas come?"},{"time":562000,"text":"Truth about that one is I had a horrible red wine hangover,"},{"time":566000,"text":"in the middle of the night, this came to me like a Xerox -- all I had to do was write it down."},{"time":569000,"text":"It was perfectly clear. I didn't do any thinking about it."},{"time":573000,"text":"And then when it ran, a lovely lady, an old lady named Mrs. Edgar Rosenberg --"},{"time":578000,"text":"if you know that name -- called me and said she loved the cover, it was so sweet."},{"time":582000,"text":"Her former name was Fay Wray, and so that was --"},{"time":587000,"text":"I didn't have the wit to say, \"Take the painting.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"Finally, this was a three-page cover, never done before,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and I don't think it will ever be done again --"},{"time":594000,"text":"successive pages in the front of the magazine."},{"time":597000,"text":"It's the ascent of man using an escalator, and it's in three parts."},{"time":604000,"text":"You can't see it all together, unfortunately, but if you look at it enough,"},{"time":607000,"text":"you can sort of start to see how it actually starts to move."},{"time":721000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"Pretty elegant. Nothing like a crash to end a joke. That completes my oeuvre."},{"time":737000,"text":"I would just like to add a crass commercial --"},{"time":740000,"text":"I have a kids' book coming out in the fall called \"Marvel Sandwiches,\""},{"time":744000,"text":"a compendium of all the serious play that ever was,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and it’s going to be available in fine bookstores, crummy bookstores,"},{"time":750000,"text":"tables on the street in October."},{"time":753000,"text":"So thank you very much."}]}]}